Step 1: Identify typical index-based iterations: `for (int i=0; i<list.size(); i++) { list.get(i) ... }`.

Step 2: Convert to enhanced for-loop:
```java
for (ElementType e : list) { ... }
```
Replace `list.get(i)` with `e`.

Step 3: If the loop uses `i` for other purposes (e.g., index calculations), skip refactoring to preserve functionality.
